PROJECT REPORT

For building my professional digital presence and technical portfolio, I have chosen LinkedIn, GitHub, and Kaggle as the main platforms. 
Each of these platforms serves a different purpose and will help me grow professionally and technically over the next four years of my academic journey.

LINKEDIN 😎🥀

LinkedIn is a professional networking platform used to create an online professional profile, similar to a digital resume. 
It allows students and professionals to connect with industry experts, recruiters, alumni, and classmates. 
LinkedIn is also used for sharing achievements, certifications, internships, projects, and professional posts. 
Over the next four years, I plan to regularly update my LinkedIn profile with my academic achievements, completed courses, certifications, and project work. 
I will also connect with professionals in the fields of Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, and Data Science to learn from their experiences and stay 
updated with industry trends. Additionally, I will use LinkedIn to search for internships and job opportunities in the future.

GITHUB 🌟🌟

GitHub is a platform used for code hosting, version control, and project management. It is very important for students in computer science and IT fields because it acts as a technical portfolio where we can showcase our programming projects and development work. On GitHub, I plan to upload my programming assignments, AI/ML projects, hackathon projects, and collaborative projects. Over the next four years, I will maintain repositories for each major project and keep updating them with improvements and documentation. This will help me build a strong coding portfolio that I can show to recruiters and professors.

KAGGLE 🌞💫

Kaggle is a platform specifically designed for data science and machine learning. It provides datasets, competitions, and notebooks where users can practice data analysis, visualization, and machine learning model building. Over the next four years, I plan to use Kaggle to practice real-world datasets, participate in competitions, and publish notebooks showing my data analysis and machine learning work. This will help me improve my practical skills in data science and build a strong profile in the AI/ML field.


Overall, these three platforms will help me build my professional network, technical portfolio, and practical skills, which will be very useful for internships, higher studies, and job opportunities in the future.
